{
  "root": {
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>What a week that was. Between the <em>Digital News Report</em> and our Masters students at City handing in their final project, it flew by. I <em>will</em> come back to the <em>DNR </em>next week, with a piece about video, but I couldn't get it done in time for today. And I also have a post about the <a href=\"https://www.vox.com/technology/2023/6/14/23760738/reddit-blackout-explained-subreddit-apollo-third-party-apps\">chaos at Reddit</a> in progress. I might even send one of them over the weekend ‚Äî but I'm always unsure about weekend newsletters. Let me know if you have strong feelings one way or another.</p><p>Anyway, let's talk about AI, because it's a little discussed subject that no-one's paying attention to‚Ä¶ üòá</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "AI Principles for Publishers",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The big difference between Generative AI and the other buzzword tech of the past few years is that people are finding practical, daily uses for it. I have never knowingly used Web3 or the Metaverse in my work ‚Äì but I do use generative AI to illustrate my posts.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In the last couple of weeks, I‚Äôve come a journalist using a personal, paid ChatGPT account in their work and another worrying that their particular skills are no longer needed. I‚Äôve seen examples of students using LLMs to generate essays (and those are just the ones that were caught‚Ä¶).",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I‚Äôm experimenting with a Slack bot that claims to assist in your SEO work. Generative AI is here, with clear use cases that make sense to ordinary people. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "That‚Äôs what those other trendy technologies never managed.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Set the rules now",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "4.0"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2023/06/assistive-intelligence-1.jpg",
        "width": 4368,
        "height": 2448,
        "caption": "The best AI is <a href=\"https://nextconf.eu/2021/06/ai-assitive-intelligence/\">assistive intelligence</a>. <em>Image by Midjourney.</em>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The last time I remember something happening quite this quickly was social media in the late 2000s. Back then, too many publishers were too slow to adopt sensible guidelines for their staff, leading to some unfortunate errors ‚Äî and consequent reputation damage. Indeed, I‚Äôd argue that our slowness then to set boundaries has led to some of the trust erosion we‚Äôre seeing now.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Watching journalists tear chuncks off each other in a partisan way on Twitter is doing nothing for our reputation for impartiality and trustworthiness.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And so, I‚Äôm bloomin‚Äô delighted to see some larger publishers getting ahead of this. Chris Moran ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "tweeted out ",
                "type": "text",
