        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This impulse to outwit and rile up folks felt weirdly at odds with the good faith and empathy you‚Äôd expect from someone in his business. In 2016, for example, Mikkelson kidded with Green on Slack that a man named Jeff Zarronandia was his best hire. ‚ÄúModel employee,‚Äù Green replied, according to screenshots. Mikkelson had made up Zarronandia a year before to troll the conservatives who insisted that Snopes was biased toward liberals. But as Snopes sought to level up, Green, then the director of business development, told Mikkelson that he thought they needed to ‚Äúclean up our loose ends.‚Äù That didn‚Äôt happen, and Zarronandia was outed as an alt in a BuzzFeed expos√© by the reporter Dean Sterling Jones.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Too many of the early internet successes were run by people with great ideas ‚Äî but without anything like the skill needed to manage a huge success. And so things spiral into ever increasing chaos.",
